As Cody padded forward, his hand slid along the haft of the pole sickle, getting a greater feel for the weapon with
each passing minute. Although he preferred his darts, he had to admit there was something reassuring about having a
pole as tall as he was between him and anything that might attack. "We're going to be friends, you and I," he
whispered, keeping the pole pointed forward at about eye level as he moved. "We're going to get along just fine."
